S I am very pleased to hear from you again. You wrote me lots of interesting information about your country, hobbies I have never heard about. I have been thinking for a long time of what would be interesting of me. Finally, an idea came to my mind. I am going to tell you about my favourite film. When I was young, I was into watching war movies and one of them is called "The letters from Ivo Yima." The main character is my favourite actor Clint Eastwood. The movie tells the story about soldiers who went to fight in an nonsense war. They were in a very difficult situation and there is no chage to escape. They spent all their time in a cave and wrote lots of letter to their families, relatives and beloved once. However, the letter have never been sent. Those letters were being hidden in sacks in the cave were they found their shelter during the war. It took more then four decades when the sacks were found. It is story based on a reality. I found out the movie really amazing and I would like to recommend to see it.
