S dear N! Long time no see, how have you been doing ? I want to go to the cinema to watch 'cry me a sad river'. Could you go with me?. Just a few minute ago,I have found the new Chinese film was directed by Quach Kinh MInh,your favourite director. It was based on a book ,which named 'Bi thuong nguoc dong thanh song'. Let I tell your about in a little more detail. A main girl has an unlucky fate,her mother accidentally cause her daughter strange disease. From my personal perspective ,she is a gentle girl who always suffers bad jokes from her friend. No one could believe her,so she decided to suicided. This film actually is very humanistic,meaningful. So I think i shoud recommend for you. Tell me your ideas,ok. your friend.
