S The popularity of video games has increased among children in recent years. To be more precise, children incline to playing of video games instead of taking part in activities such as sport which is the key factor in their devolopment. In a view of receant discusions, we can hear arguments that support the idea of playing video games. On the other side, there are also negative arguments. From my point of view, playing video games has a positive impact on children mind. To give an illustration, it support their ability to react quickly and take an immediate decision. Secondly, it also develop their imagination in many situations and help them to solve problems such as school tasks. The negative impact of playing video games is described by parents as an inability to solve fundamental tasks relating to our daily life. That is to say, the tasks in which its difficulty is adecvate to the age of children. Secondly, the vaste of time is a second reason. All things considered, it seems reasonable to assume the fact, the our chidren grow up in the 21st century and it is hard to steer clear of the upcoming technology. We are witnessing that our chidren will be dependable on new technology \u2013 in a round about kind of way.
