S Dear town council, I heard that there are intensive discussions among the town council members about banning mobile phone usage on public transportation, in shops and restaurants. I assume advantages and disadvantages of this plan have been thoroughly evaluated by experts. Along with that, I would like to express my strong disagreement to this plan as a tax payer, too. To begin with, it is too drastic for people to adjust their current ways to work and manage daily activities if the ban comes into force. Use of mobile phone has been inevitable social infrastructure for the past three decades. Without it, I think that productivity at work will be decreased, even though the ban is effective within limited areas. Another reason is that people nowadays need to reach someone as well as to be reachable whenever they need from anywhere due to security reasons. For instance, parents, who are still heading back home on a commuter train, will be relieved when they receive a call from their children at home. Another example is that children, whose aging parents live remotely, will be seriously worried about the parents\u2019 health condition when their parents do not answer the cell phone, who might be simply eating out at that time. Having say that, I maintain the idea that appropriate phone usage should be kept for good manners in public places. My suggestion is to introduce dedicated times and dates for specified places or zones where using mobile phones triggers server punishment. I firmly believe that the idea of banning mobile phones in such areas is still not ready for the above reasons. It would be greatly appreciated if the council members would reconsider the plan. Best regards, AAAA BBBB
