S There are too many doctors working in big citys, conclusive some of them are rendundant. However, on the contrary side too little are working on the countryside. This is an controversal topic, that desperately needs to be solved immediately. Otherwise, the situation that sick people do not have a doctor in their town is imminent. Every single town needs a doctor and due to the reason that this is such a pressing matter, there are some solutions. Nevertheless, it is undeniable important to know why doctors in rural areas are thin on the ground, striktly speaking none of the freshly graduated doctros is willing to move in small villages. They simply earn to little. There can be no doubt that a doctor can medicate more people in big citys than in small towns, conclusively it is more profitable for them working in the city. One possiblility to ensure more doctors in rural areas might be a shorter study time, or a reduction of the tuition. Thereby, expecially those who do not have the neccassery money might take the opportunity. It would be a great chance for the towns as well as for the doctors. Alternitively, the towns inhabitants need to pay the doctors an annual fee. There can be no doubt that they want to have a doctor in the vicinity, in the end the inhabitants of each town would be responsible for they're doctor, it would be a egragious chance. Most people think that moving away from citys is unattractive. Revamping the mostly old towns might change that opinion. Another pheripheral side effect is that the living qulity in these towns would increase tremendously. Taking all these aspect into consideration, there can be do doubt that there are some solutions for current situation, which definitely needs to be solved.
