S A few months ago I have discovered a useful tool for writing in English language called \u201EWrite and Improve\u201C. However, but it is not the only tool I use for practicing of my writing. As a second tool I use \u201EGrammarly\u201C. Both of them provide its writers final score of their results and include different ways of settings for the writing and assessment. If I can make a recommendation, I would say both of them have an advantages and disadvantages. Firstly, the tool Write and Improve is sectioned in four levels of progress from the beginner to advanced. Finishing a certain amount of tasks is awarded. Function of each award is your support to start a new writing task to reach the next award. Each writing task you have finished is checked and your mistakes can be corrected. As a result of your work you will see a reached level of each your finished task. In addition, the tool offers services like checking of your writing by a teacher or participation in a class where you can provide your advice to other students. Simultaneously, you can share your own task you created for others. Secondly, the tool Grammarly is used by writers without possibility of creating writing tasks or to answer them. This tool is completely different from Write an Improve. It can only check your writing and it offers you a correction of your mistakes. In order to use this tool more effectively is to make a setting for the purpose of your writing goals. All things considered, as a result of my recommendation I would say the tool Write and Improve is much more useful for students of English of different levels. Conversely, Grammarly seems to be the most useful tool for those who use English in their work. For example, to write a business letter or write an essay on topic you want.
