S One of the subjects in schools is a music, which plays a key role to wake up students emotions and learn them to think much deeper. It also helps to understand things around us and finally, it boosts your brain activity. To put it in another way, schools trying to find talents throughout this method of learning. However, thare are different stands of schools in learning of music. Approximately 35 per cent of schools required playing a musical instruments as well. To be more precise, all students in the class have to play a musical instruments. Conversely, the rest of schools do not required playing a musical instrument on its students. A good illustration of this is in primary schools, where their students are prepared for higher level of education such as in University or High school. From the arguments stated above, I see reasonable to give students a choice, whether they want to learn music and simultaneously play a musical instrument or not. If I were in a position of the director of a school, I would have given them a choice. From my view, playing a musical instrument should be optional and studying music should be considered only for students up to third class in primary schools.
