S I am writing to apologize you for that I did not replied immediately to you letter. However, I was on holiday for three weeks with my new girlfriend. You asked me in your last letter about a review of a movie I love the most. Well, the film I am fond of every time I see it is a movie from well known film maker Clint Eastwood and the movie is called the Letters from Ywo Gima. It is about ordinary men who have been sent to fight in a none sense war. All of them died in a battlefield and lots of them committed suicide. What is more, before they died they wrote letters to their family members, relatives or the love once. Those letters had never been sent off. Instead they have been hidden in the caves in the island and have been found after 50 years. Clint Eastwood wrote the movie based on those letters. It is a real story that make you feel whit those soldiers who died in a terrible war. I do hope you will be very amazed by the story and reality that comes from the letters. We can not imagine that in a real situation.
