S I was playing video games in my teenage specifically PlayStation one and it was a very exciting at that time and also there was a conflict with my mother because we were playing more than four hours daily and she was so angry with us, so I understand the concerns of parents about children behavior with video games by the addiction on it and urge their sons to balance in their life. Video games are so attractive to play and for me, I see it as a personal experience where affect to som of them negatively via spending many hours on it and that kind of play lead to defect in balance and severe weakness in social communication and lack of concentration. On the other hand, maybe video games grow programming skills and perhaps be in it benefit financial and therefore become a profession and source of income. Now video games became an industry that loves it wide supporters around the world so parents have to deal with it more realistically and try to be close with their sons in order to limit to negative effects and support their hobbies without collision.
