S About keeping animals in zoos, I don't think it's really good because animals belong to the nature and if you need to learn something about animals you can just read some specific books or search it on the internet, or seeing some TV programs about them. But it's true too that zoos are pretty good for basic information about animals like their living zone or the food they eat seen with your eyes but they should be in the nature. I just think that animals belong in nature and it is wrong to keep them in zoos,because they aren't living good in the zoos as in their habitat. See polar bears as an example, they can't live good in the zoos because they are from Antartic or some ner places but not in the zoos that are in cities. And there are a lot of animals that doesn't eat as good as in their habitat because there isn't the food they eat.
