S Unhealthy lifestyle has began to influence the life of the students both in university and school. One of them is inactive lifestyle. It indeed brings severe impacts on the students' lifestyle. Several efforts have been proposed as one of them is forcing them to do sports activities at least 3 three times in a week. However, would it create the impact? First of all, doing exercise is beneficial for the body as it can bring positivies to the students. However, bear in mind that every student has its own right for its own body. They can do whatever they want with their bodies as they can choose whichever lifestyle they are going to implement as the responsibilities are on them. Doing exercise is one the choices they can make. Therefore, Encouraging them to do sports would be better than making it mandatory. Second of all, healthy lifestyle is not all about physical activities such as do sports or exercise. It is truly important to have a healthy lifestyle. However, doing sports is not always the case to have a healthy life. There are many other activities that can bring the students to have healthy life such as diet, food choices or meditations. Third of all, it is irrelevant to force the students to do sports three times a week. The healthy lifestyle is not defined by quantity of exercises in a week done by a person. But it is more to the quality of the exercise. It would be less relevant to have exercise for three times in a week without having a good quality of activities than just once with impacts to the students. Besides, the students are generally busy with their own courseworks and extracurricular activities as it becomes a hindrance for them to do exercies if it being upheld. In conclusion, forcing students to do sports every week might bring good impact on them. However, it contradics to their rights and potentially impedes their activities. Encouraging them to do exercise is actually more preferred than making it compulsary.
