S I guess that like any other activity, there has to be boundaries. And those boundaries have to be given to children by their parents. Too much video game could be harmful for their sight, could jeopardize their studies, their grades at school and it\u00B4s not good for their healthy. It\u00B4s because it\u00B4s not recommend for their bodies to stay at the some position for so many hours. So, I think that playing video game can be a hobby and like any other hobby it couldn\u00B4t take of you many hours in the day. They should play video games only if they\u00B4ve already done their homeworks, if they\u00B4ve already studied and if they\u00B4ve already done their list of must do chores of the day. There are other things that should be considered. There are games too violent that could affect children\u00B4s mind. So, the parents should be aware of that too and, from the time to time , they should just take a fast look on their children\u00B4s games.
