S I think that studying abroad can give you lots of great experiences and could also make you more independent. But I think that the most advantage is the opportunity of knowing yourself far away from the look of your parents, family and friends. It gives you the freedom of discovering sides of you that you didn\u00B4t know of. Some of them you will enjoy and some of them you won\u00B4t, but you can work on those that you didn\u00B4t like it and make a better version of yourself. The knowdledge among with this is also a huge experience. The school\u00B4s structure and the educational system will be different and you will have to adjuste yourself in this whole new world. The colleagues will be probably from differents countries and the differents cultures among with it will give you personal and professional growth. Of course that there isn\u00B4t only advantages. You will be alone in a country where is only stranges cultures and people. I think that you will feel loneliness, specially in the first months, but if you think ahead about the advantages and stay strong, you will be alright.
