S As I\u00B4m not satisfied with my grades and my commitment last year, I want to work harder this year. I plan to make a daily routine of at least twenty minutes per day for each subject that I\u00B4ve had that day. This goal is because I\u00B4ve read in a newspaper or I\u00B4ve heard somewhere that it\u00B4s needed 10 minutes of studying per day if you want to improve in something. So, I guess that 20 minutes is beyond fine. I should pay more attention on those subjects that I don\u00B4t like because they are also those which I fail most in the tests. So, here they are: geography, history and biology. I think it\u00B4s because they practily only have the reading part, so I get bored easily. I need exercise to ensure that I understood the content and theory. If I stay only in the reading it feels so monotous for me and I end up giving up and moving on to the subjects that I\u00B4m more familiar to like chemistry, physics and mathematic.
