S Some might say that students and teachers can have the same relationship on a virtuallity way and the learning process wouldn\u00B4t be jeopardize, but the pandemic came to ensure that it\u00B4s not entirely true. Then, teachers and students will still have to go to an educational building. However, theories and knowledge will be given to students in a completely different way. The technology will play an important part on the learning path transforming it onto a funnier and more interesting option for all. The three-dimension can be used in subjects like art or history and therefore students will be able to experience a tour at hundreds of museums at many different coutries without leaving the classroom. It can also be added to biology. Mechanical animals, build by the latest technology, have a striking resemblance to the real ones. So, with a hidden camera, they can be insert onto its natural habitat and transmit their videos caption to a computer. With it, students can learn how animals behave and live naturally.
