S Television is often used as an entertainment tool, but it can also provides society culture and knowledge in different fields and through an easier and more interesting way. For example, there are already cartoons which adds educational cadres into their normally sequence or educational statements to their characters. These has been a good critique from parents whom have been watching his children learning about numbers, colours, animals, new vocabulary and so many other things. There are channels which are only commited to an interesting subject such as history, animals or technology. They provide bunch of documentaries, videos and discussions about the topics. These can offer sometimes extra information for those who were already familiar with the subject or can be an introduction for those who didn\u00B4t know anything about it. When it comes to a visual and hearing information, sometimes the brain captures and keeps it more easily. The really question is if the person is willing to spend his time on this type of channels.
