S Giove, a little village in Umbria, the green heart of Italy. Giove is about 100 kilometers from Rome and there is a train station. This village is very famous thanks to his big medieval castle. The castle has 365 windows, one for each day of the years. In Giove you can eat in several typical restaurants but there is not souvenir shops or other kind of shops. Sometimes the citizen organised village festivals for tourists. It is a beautiful location. Let's go!
