S This it's a very controversial theme because for me tell always the truth is very imporatnt but in some cases it's important to say any lies. I think that it's a metter of perspective, there are many sitiations in the cotidian life where you have to say lies to can resolve the problem or can achieve some things. Currently the lies has become part of our life and behaviors and it's almost impossible not say any lie however insignificant it may be. I considered my self like an honest person and for me tell the truth in any moment it's very important and necessary for my values but I had to tell lies in many situatios too and not for that reason I think that i'm a bad person. For example: If in a work interview somebody ask me about my skills and my experience in the area for which I'm applying, I must to tell the truth, untill I want to get the job, it's necessary to tell the truth to the interviewer because won't be honest from my part say lies to get the job. Another example where may be to tell a lie it's necessary, If my mother ask me to go to the super markt to buy food and vegetables and I forgot buy the potatoes I have to tell her that in the supermark there weren't none of the ones of she buys to cook, so, that lie no afect nothing and not for that I'll consider like a lier.
