S Studying abroad is a great opportunity and incredible experience. However, every student who like to study for a while in another country should consider many aspects those are commonly left out. I think we should have clear, why we want to do it and if we really are ready to such experience. Sometimes the objective of studying abroad is not clear and we only think it is a journey to know another country and when we are there as student, not as tourist, some difficulties come up and they can make our time there hard. Besides, when we only think about enjoying that new experience, we usually forget that we are there to study, we have a huge responsabilty, not only with ourselves but we with all people who gave us that chance, because we represent our university and country. On the other hand, when we decide studying abroad after thinking all responasbilities, costs, difficulties and posible bad or good experience, we are ready to really enjoy that opportunity as student. Studying abroad can be gratifying and such a learning experience like no other, but it also can be sometimes awkward, complicated and lonely. If you really want to go out your comfortable zone and you are ready to face differents situations, you should studying abroad.
