S About doing volunteer work, I'm not against it, but if I ruled an high school I wont force my students to do some volunteer work because helping isn't that much important (for graduation) it can grow your final mark but for example, if you try to do a volunteer job because you're forced to do it to graduate, then you can't go and then you couldn't do it and you fail because that, it would make many people anger just for that. But in other parts doing volunteer work would make more people charismatic and with eager to help more people without the needing of a reward, and that's good. Not in all cases it goes well, but I mean, doing those work is mostly common to foment the believing in that helping could make more people happier. In conclusion I won't force students to do some volunteer work to graduate, but just to make their marks better.
