S l think l believe and agree that putting animals in a zoo is not so good,and l am pretty sure that l'm not alone. There's a lot of sciencists out there who think my point of view is right. Here's my proof: First,our humans are never satisfied by the things they'd done and still want to get more answers from nature. But does it make it better? No. Our planet were just getting worser and worser. One time,our dear old America had it's first human caused species wipe out. It happend at 2006 July 24th,when the last Red Tailed Do-do bird had been shot down by Arnold Plamer. Now let's first get to topic. Keeping animals from nature will lost the animals's nature. Soon,it will not survive in this world anymore. Even tigers and lions that day will be killed by just a little insect. Then people will ask:"Why?" Easy,because they'd been in locked in cages so long,they even forgot how to use their hunting skills and how to roar.
