S The first discussion that appears is the importance and the utility of the money. The money can give us stability, comfort and pleasure of conquering the most beautiful and unique material possession in the world. But beauty is a subjective matter and if you don\u00B4t have enough time to enjoy the rewards of your richness, what is the point of having the biggest bank account? It is true that money can\u00B4t buy healthy because our human body has still so many misteries to solve and there are so many parts of our organism which are untouchable and that we can\u00B4t understand yet. So, the money won\u00B4t matter when you have something that is not decipherable. On the other hand, if you are healthy, you can work hard to achieve the social status aimed. Money is something tangible, but healthy sometimes can be something impossible to achieve. So, if you could choose between richness and healthy, what would it be?
