S In the last years some students attending high school or university decide to study some time in a foreign country instead of studying at home. This decision will obviously impact their life with pros and cons. Although nowadays it seems to be an easy choice to take, deciding to study in a foreign country is not that simple. First of all we have to consider the costs, quite high; secondly the psychological impact has a great component in the final result: students have to adapt to a new life and at the same time to attend the school, hopefully, with good outcomes, not an easy situation to cope with. On the other hand, the possibility to study abroad represents a great opportunity that someone shouldn't miss. Learning a foreing language in the origin country is much better than studying it in another place, it gives the possibility to improve it day-by-day with live language and apprehend at the same time the local way of living, a good start, envisioning to live abroad in the future. In the end, I think that the decision of studying for some time abroad is a very positive decision even just to consider simply the broader possibilities of future jobs.
