S The Future of Travel is a topic argument nowadays! Due to the pandemic, habits have changed a lot and while someone could still persist to believe that travelling will be as easy as in the past, some others are deeply aware of the dramatic changes in the whole world of traveling. Once, for example, we could plan to fly abroad for a holiday by simply choosing the country and reserving the flights, all of this without being forced to consider the quarantine required nowadays on the coming back and the additional information about the health conditions compulsory if we want take a plane. Under this light, the usual fortnight spent for a normal summer holiday will be no longer enough. We will therefore need to add the days for the restriction and moreover some other days for medical checks. On the other hand, we shall be able to travel safely in remote places such as on the peaks of the mountains or on the outer sea maybe on a private sailing boat for a relaxing vacation. These two options, very expensive today, will be certainly much cheaper as they will be more requested in comparison to the past. Despite of all, travel will remain one of the most attractive human habits!
