S Personally, I'd prefer living a long, calm life until 100 years than living a short'n exciting live, well, depending on how many years you'd live I could change my opinion because a long life and a calm life is very good if you need to relax for studying or for work, but a short and exciting live could be very-very funny. I rather the long, calm life until 100 than a short life because I really like living relaxed days than exciting days because I won't know what could happen after that day, but living a calm live I could predict in some ways what could happen, and I prefer that, and in the job I like to work in, I could work more efficiently knowing that in the next day it will go good, a bad point in living a long live is that if you do not like nothing in your life and you don't really like what you're doing that day-week-month-year that could be very bad but you can end your life in some sort of ways, some more painfully ways and other painless. If I had to choose one of them, I'd choose the long and calm life, as I am a relaxed person but unfortunately my life isn't that much calm. So for trying a calm life, I would choose a long and calm life.
