S In this article today we are going to talk about the future of schools, in particular in which extent they might change or not in a tomorrow not too distant. Based on the broad development of information technology we tend to believe that in a not distant future, schools, as we know them today, will certainly disappear. For instance, the figure of teachers will be replaced by an artificial intelligence who through the computer screen will teach students all over the world. Thanks to this, supposing that all the students will have access to an electronical device, the percentage of analphabets could be sensibly lowered. What could instead remain the same as of today, hopefully, it will be the students'curiosity for new topics, their wish of deepening their knowledge and the desire of exploring the world. In the end, I believe that despite of the change that will certainly happen in the future, the schools whatever ways they will be organized will still foster the right environment to broaden the knowledge and leverage the skills of all students and of all those who will feel like studying at all ages.
