S Most medial doctors want to work in the big cities in order to make a lot of money or to have a good living. In my country many doctors want to work in the biggest and the fastest growing cities. They are struggeling to remain in those cities. In the public helth care it doesn't matter if you are working as a doctor in a big city or in a small. You have the same sallary. Furthermore, if you work in a small city you will have less work to do and the rent will be cheaper but everyone prefers to stay in an good developed city even is they pay much more for it. I think this problem could pe solved if the medical doctors will be resigned in cities that are close to their parents house or if the reallocation will be made based on grades. As a result you cannot choose to wok in an hospital from a big city that has only medical doctors with 10 as a grade if you have a seven.
