S In our planet lost of species are endangered, a considerable percentage of wild animals is at risk of extinction and under this light zoos seem to be the last resort for them to survive. Some people could disagree being those animals born free, they may argue that they should keep living that way. I like thinking that wild species should spend their whole life in the native environment. I feel it's innatural to force them living in a different place out of their native one. For instance, it is unacceptable that a lion accustomed to the heath of savana must be trapped in a zoo in a northern region. Or another example, is to constrain dolphins living in the limited area of a swimming pool. Although this might be the only possibility for few animals not to become extinct, I still insist on the principle to let them live wild and free. Zoos may be a nice place for children who can get to know creatures that they barely meet in normal circumstances. Though a good footage, performed in the animals' original world could do the same. Once more, I keep thinking that animals should live in the spots where they were born, however, as long as the human beings continue to disrespect other living beings on this planet, the zoos might remain the only viable alternative to save those lives from extiction.
