S Lots people think that good school results are only granted if teachers do not change over the years; some others believe that a change amid the teachers over the years can be more beneficial. I would start by setting a time range as students have needs differentiated by age: pupils in the primary school certainly need to have a referred point , one teacher to apply to not only for school subjects but also as reference for their psychological growth. In the secondary school, instead, in my opinion, students need a change, they need to differentiate references: they will have to begin and face the alternative nuances that life could offer and what a good opportunity by starting at school, with a teacher per each subject! At College, we have grown-up students and definitely, this is the best stage in which they can enrich their culture, they can enlarge their life vision by embrancing the differet view points thanks to many professors. I strongly believe that the richness of human beings, lays in the variety, in any respect! BH
