S Volunteer work seems to be a compulsory request for a few high schools for their students to graduate. I believe that this is a fair and important step for the students and their growth, emotionally and professionally speaking. This requirement can certainly help students to better understand the real world out of the school environment . To most of them, first of all, it might give the opportunity to really get in touch with other realities, sometimes very different from their families and their usual way of living. Secondly they can have a sample of the job's world with all its duties and responsibilities. Besides they might as well decide that it could be the job they would like to do in the future as a living. For instance, they could volounteer in a kinder garden and realize that taking care of children and is the aim of their life. Or, another example, helping old people in their daily routine might push some scholars to decide and form in a job that involves the cure and care of the elders. Although they are not paid for this kind of activity, I strongly believe that they will receive much more in terms of learning and formation. I would definitely recommed to all students to work volountary while studying in order to widen their horizons and grow as a person and as citizen.
