S My name is Josh and I am writing to give a better aproach of the no mobile phones new law. I heard on the news that the use of mobile phones will be banned in some public places, shops and restaurants. I think this approach is a little madness. I am positive that we can find another one. For example in the restaurants could be an unwritten rule to obey. The rule will be like "Who is staying on the phone, will pay de bill." In the public transport if you stay on the phone and you are seated, you have to give the seat to sombody else. In the shop if you stay on the phone, you have to give your place from the que to somebody else. The use of phones cannot be banned because many people have many problems. Maybe they want to talk with their sick child or their sick mother or it's an urgency and they must call 911. I am also anxios to find out what is the main reason for this law. There must be something that got into the city's hall nerves. In the end I will like to say that in the future the city hall must be more carefull with the new laws because lately, we all laugh of the new laws.
