S Music at school. Music as a school subject or how to learn and play an instrument is compulsory in a few schools while in some others, students are not required to do so. I think that music should always be added as subject to learn in each school at any level being far important to the emotional growth of scholars and as alternative way of learning about history. Just to give an example, learning about the history of music may give the students the possibility to know about a part of human evolution. Only to name the period of romanticism and studying about Wagner could make them undertand the vision of the intellectuals in the nineteenth century. In addition , learning how to play an instrument can definitely help the development of a manual intellegence as well as a sensitive one in most of the students. Altough listening to music can be relaxing, learning how to play it might become a more effective tool to use when you need to get rid of the stress. In conclusion, I underline again the importance of studying music as a school subject at any degree because it will enrich the students' inner world, it will broaden their emotional horizon and will add another communication skill. Music is absolutely another language which can easily talk to heart and soul.
