S There is a heated debate for many years on availability of medical care in rural areas. Many doctors left thiese areas to provide medical in big cities. What is more, those who were old retired. If this trend continue, the situation will not be sustainable. What this means in practical term is that rural ares would not be able to provide proper medical servises in the region. To solve that problem, we have to deal with arguments that cause this lack of medical care. Let us to unpack some of them. Financial problems is one of them. A regular income that is provided to doctors in rural areas is not efficient do cover all services linked to providing medical care. Secondly, other reason is attractiveness of the area. Lack of infrastructure, for example. Infrastracture and transportation system is playing an important role. If we want to tacle with that problem successfuly, wehave to provide a proper background.
