S I don't know how to aproach thi subject. It is odd to ask a person if he wants to live long or intense because everyone wants both. Regarding the answer I have to give, it depends on the type of life. I wouldn't like to live only 20 years and intense but I also wouldn't like to live 100 years and to be like a robot. The way I see it, a good life is one lived with balance. I see myself living intense not like a robot but also not like a morone. To give an example: I would defently go to parties but not to get in a coma from alchool. This word "intese" have to have it's own boundries. We have to live intense with responsability. I also don't see myself in the other extreme. I have friends who dosen't like to fly because they are scared of earplanes, but we both know that is safer in the air. I am a man who likes the put balance in everything, especially in life. I don't like to be extreme, even if is about the left or the ight part of the boundary. We all have to live an intense life but with responsability and in this way we'll live a long and intense life and we will achieve everything we propose.
