S Studying at university is an important choice in life and as a consequence, in relation to the chosen school, it is sometimes necessary to move from home. Some students decide then to leave home and stay on their own while some others choose to stay by their families. The first decisive factor establishing whether to stay or go is the economical aspect which determines as well the choice of the univerisity to attend. In my opinion, I would suggest to stay home with parents so that students can totally dedicate their time to studies instead to try and balance sudies and job. Thinking just about the school may help to get over the university in due time. If, on the contrary, students decide to leave home and live by themeselves while studying, they have first of all to consider the additional cost of a rented apartment. Then, they need to start and think their life as an adult with all the consequeces of a life far from parents. For example, they definitely need to look after their new house, think on how to arrange the daily routine such as shopping for meals or cleaning the house. All actions that subtract time from their studying. In addition to it, should they need to look for a job to gain a living, they will have lesser time for school. In some cases, this situation can lead the students to withdraw from university. In the end, I strongly believe that the best and the most effective way to study at the University is to choose a school not very far from parents' home in order to stay with parents and dedicate all the energy towards the successful conclusion of the school career.
