S An environment that provides comfort and silence it\u00B4s almost always the perfect condition for any worker at a work place. When you give privacy to an employee, he feels comfortable, calm, relaxed and safe. Those characteristics remind him of his home and because of that, he will be more openned and free to be himself out of the looks, pressure and critical expressions and words of his coworkers. This relaxed area will induce his criativity and productivity. The results of an enclosed workstation will appear at the quality of the work presented by the employees and also at the amount and agility of the tasks done by him daily. On the other hand, those offices with open design don\u00B4t have walls which can provide privacy to the employees. The privacy that comes with the walls offers a distancy of critical looks from coworkers and also offers a certain sound barrier between them. The lack of sound barrier is probably one of the main reasons why workers get so distracted during his daily work. When you are at a place that you don\u00B4t feel comfortable to do your job, it can be quite challenging to concentrate enough to start a task. When you finally got back on track, someone starts talking on the phone or with someone near yout. That action disturbs anyone even the most focused person and you will get a hard time trying to keep going with your work. Even though when those conversations are over, you will spent another few minutes to get back to the rythm and the level of concentration that you were before you were interrupted. Those precious minutes attached to the loss of focus daily, will for sure affect the productivity and quality of the entire office.
