S Dear Cassie, Thank goodness you didn't go to the concert. I almost risked my life for it! Now just let me get this straight. l was in my own seat and enjoying Judy Blume's music when three men wearing black and holding a gun in their hands ran inside,and yelled:"Freeze! Or l'll shoot!" Everyone turned around,and no one dared to move a muscle. Even Judy Blume stopped playing. We're like a herd of deers caught in a headlight. After one minute,a men ran out of the back door a escaped. I was the second one to go,l had to be sneaky to make l didn't make a big racket. When l finally escaped,l went straight to the S. W. A. T office. They took those guys to the Supreme Court,and nobody was badly hurt. Except that woman who had been shot in the breast. Anyway,it was a tramatizing experience for sure. ln fact,l was still trembling in my bed when l was sending you this letter. Moby
