S In every corner of the world, there is someone who knows a talented person who could have been an incredible profession if it was given him the opportunity to develop this gift. It is known that it\u00B4s never too late to accomplish great things, but in some areas this truth it is not applied like in the world of the sports. Even though some people take that statement as a mantra in their lives, others think that those words belong only to a fairy tale world. These people don\u00B4t think that the option to dive into a new profession and left behind years of commitment and dedication to the profession that they have been working on since they can remember it\u00B4s a valid one. And I can\u00B4t blame them because the unknown can be really terrifying and this fear may be bigger than the wish to feel connected to their inner truth. We are often wasting thousands of talents because we don\u00B4t offer the opportunity to each one of them to find out their calling. One solution to this error could be found and corrected through programs at schools. Schools need to offer to the students diverse programs of dance, sports, music and other areas so that they can choose themselves which one they are more connected and comfortable on doing it. Those programs should be a part of their educational system as an obligation subject. At that age, adolescents and children have to be sometimes encouraged to make a move because science already confirmed that the part of our brain related to making decisions it is not fully developed until 18 years old. That being said, all the students should experience all kinds of classes like music classes. If they found out during those periods that they don\u00B4t have the talent or they don\u00B4t want to pursue it in their lives, they can bring this new hability to their daily lives as a hobby. Music is always welcome in anyone\u00B4s lives. It can give us piece of mind, change our mood,help us to concentrate and help us to overcome and release a feeling that has been harming us and jeopardizing our growth.
