S It's more important to be healthy to be rich. I follow and respect this statement,but there are a touch. How can you be healthy when you are poor? Like,if your family had no money,then how do you keep yourself healthy? You'd starve to death. Or,if you sit on road,begging others to throw money into your cup,you'd be very weak because the disease lying around the street ground. So if you are poor but healthy you still will be weak. That's way when Barack Obama got to be president,he had a prgramm called BamaCare. It's about if one people got invovled in a terrible accident and the person was badly hurt,the medical expenses will be mostly paid by the government if it's diffcult to pay at once. But let's look at the different side. If you are very wealthy but not healthy,you still can recover by eating pills and resting. After all,money can particularly buy anything. Except money,people,and time. So the statement"It is more important to be healthy than to be rich." is partly not true.
