S First,l have to point out that l had no offense or enemy-ship with HUAWAI,MIX,oppo and vivo (ICYMI, these are all big electronics companys). But my theory is that electronics can never replace something in the eduacational board. Or at least,not completly. If you ask me,Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities? My answer is that it depends on how you use it. l mean,it is possible that computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities as long as everyone knows how to use it properly. You open your iphone,and instead of studying,you open a game. Then in this case,computers and tablets absoutly,completely can't replace books in schools and universities. But if you open your hybrid school website,and you study very hard,then computers and tablets can completely replace books in schools and universities. So it really depends on who you are and what you are going to do on the electronic device.
