S Dear town council, I wrote this letter because 15 families from Star Street had chosen me to be delegate, this letter contains all Star Streets villigers emotions, feelings and thoughts. I have been living in this town for 70 years. I was born in this town. Me and my family's daily routines were very diffucult when I was a child. There were no technological devices, machines for farming and communicating devices but that was 65 years ago. I and many of town members wish to had some technology. There were different members in town councils in those years. One day they asked us if we wanted to have telephones. Then they said they would get the substructure ready for telephone lines. On that day we got used to use mobile phones everywhere. We all thought if these mobile phones hadn't be used everywhere we would have had very hard life. We all had been using our mobile phones happily before this bad idea was clarified by town council. Many of us have children, relatives and grandchildren who live in city centers; we want to communicate with them easily in everywhere. We like our town's development. We all agree that we have a right to make phone calls, send messages to put it simple use mobile phone. We don't want you to introduce that kind of law in our town. Best regards, Eva Sparks and The Star Street Villigers.
