S Nowadays, the internet and homestead lifestyle contribute to the inactive lifestyle, the citizens can without step out the door but get the takeaway and all of the things that life necessity, so somebody come up with a idel that all university students and school children should be forced to do sports at least 3 times per week. As far as I'm concerned, I can't agree with this idea, it is good to promote national exercise, but should not be forced but should be channelled. First and foremost, people of all ages have something they must to do, like the students, they have to prepare for the term final exam, and the fresh man need study hard to get credits, and the graduated may have prepare for interview and work hard untill steady so that they can't do sprots, so, it will intensify many society contradictions, moreover, it may causing trouble for a lot of people. Additionally, there are varity of approaches to deal with national inactive lifestyle phenomenon but not the only way to force students and children work out at least 3 times every week, for example, the government can hold some citizens games, or shot some promote video to encourage the individuals work out frequently which can benefit them a lot, all these way are better than force them to do sports. What's more, teenagers and childrens may have the reble mentality, and I convince that if government wanna to enforce some policies, some punitive measures are bound to be enacted, in that case, some family don't want their children be punished, so they will force them to do sports which teenagers and childrens don't want to do, so the gaps of renlationship will appeare which will lead to truancy rate surge, and finally cuase the suicide rate increase. All in all, I know it is critical to improve national physical fitness,and make the young love the feel of go outside but not sit in concret-and-steal facade construction all the day, but may some better options could be chosen.
