S Since first human settlements music has been part of their lives. Several archaeological evidences show different types of musical instruments in each culture discovered until now. These cultures created their own music and instruments to play it. So, music looks to be essential demostration in human life. Music has been important in groups of people as a demostration of identity and support like anthems, songs to celebrate battles, songs to remember ancestors and to celebrate newborns. Further, music has escorted historical events around the world and new music joins to support new social claims and movements. Probably, the reason why music is part of all these human aspects, is because music makes us feel more. Each emotion is boost with music, some kind of music make us feel powerful, other makes us feel happy, other makes us feel sad and other make us feel proud. Even though there are some types of music which make us feel all emotions with a single song. Thus, music is a loyal partner in our lives, it is magic which enter by our ears, it is transformed and come out like corporal movements and sensations. Without music human life would be boring and gray.
