S Yes, learning a foreign language is important today because the world is more connected than ever before. Nowadays, people talk to others who are in different places around the world, and they fell confortable doing so. English is the most used language to communicate with other people when you are in a foreign country, but Chinese will be used more and more in the future. If you work for a global company, you need to learn English, knowing a foreign language is essential to get a job in a multinational corportation. In the past, the internet was not well developed, we had fewer tools to communicate with other people, and we basically used cell phones to talk long distance. Our parents work in local companies so they didn't need to speak another language, but the reality has changed and today everyone needs to know a foreign language to work. I think that in the future, leaning a language will be easier, with the advent of new tools we will learn English easily than in past.
