S Many would say that an intense brief existence could be harsh to choose if they were given the opportunity to make a choice, but I would definetely opt for it. I would take the chance to go back in time, rewind my life and restart from the beginning to live each and every single moment as it were the last. I am thrilled by the etymology of life, a concept bound to energy, and the latter, an essence that all human beings have inherited. Energy generates life, in a circle that is timeless and infinite. From its realistic point of view I see a short lifespan as a concentration of feeling and emotions submerged by a flood of experiences and events that most of the historical figures like poets, writers, scientists have lived. I would prefer leaving a trace and make my life an exciting trip and be able to experience as much as I could in order to make my family, my friends and my acquaintances proud of me. My still young life taught me that deep emotions inevitably bring struggle, pain, disappointment, uncertainties and agony, but life would not be as beautiful as it is without them. There is a need to know that the bright side of our life comes next when we disappear and live our essence and energy in the memory of what we did. I live mine in the same way, rush of feelings, even though i don't know how long it will last.
