S The best holiday I ever had was the Cristmas of 2018, I were in Uruguay in this holiday on a roadtrip. We had been arrived in Montevideo at the holiday when we noticed that had nothing opened, we have nowhere to lunch or a place to buy food or meals. This was not a problem, because I and my wife could sightseing around the city without traffic, we saw many beautiful places and in the night, we ate bread with turkey pate because there wasn't opened restaurants. It was the best holiday I ever had because there was no people in the streets, we could walked alone in the city, and drove in empty roads, we could move through the streets as fast as possible, and we knew all city in one day. We do our entire tourist rout in few days we planned do, then we could go to another city in the same roadtrip, we went to Buenos Aires in Argentina, that was really a good holiday and we enjoy every momento at that day.
