S Some people believe that it is good for students to have the same teacher for several years. Others think students benefit more from having new teachers each year. I think both options is good, when the students have the same teacher for several years, they will understand the model of teaching that teacher have and will adapt themselves to focus more in the lessons than in things like the uncertainity about what teacher will they have in the next class. Nonetheless, have different teachers is good too, when the students have new teachers every year, they might be more sociable compared to other students, they adapt themselves to other realities, have other opinions and ppints of views, and are more adapted to real live situations when they will meet new people every day. How I argue, the fist or the second option have benefits and issues, the better option is to choose a hibrid model, mixing the both options to improve the students knoledge and adapt them to different situations. We can choose on only teacher for the first five years of the student and after make them choose a different teacher every year, in this model we can have the benefitis of the two options and reduce the bias we could have adoption only one option. If we analise our learning model, we can see a lack of opportunities of learning that restricts the skill of students just because we don't think about our learning models, we need try something different to have differente results. Think about the possibilities we have today if we use the digital tools that are available, we have the chance to create a model that realy changes the way we learn things. Think about it.
