S Some people believe zoos are good places for people to learn about animals, these people usually think about the benefits for children to see animals live and improve their knoledge about the animal's habits and behaviors. But these same people don't think about the animals needs, capture and animal to expose in a Zoo is cruel and need be prohibited by the governments, don't make sense remove an animal from the nature to put it in a jail for people see it in a place. Other people believe animals belong in nature and it is wrong to keep them in zoos. These people think the animals need be free and the humans have no rights to rest these animals in jails just for human fun. The problem with this point of view is the distance that will be create between people and animals. When people see the animals, they engage themselves to preserve them, and this is good for society and for the planet. I have no oppinion about this discussion because both arguments are good enough to convince me. I think we can adopt a middle term to benefit both sides of society, we can create zoos only with animals that have no possibility to return to nature, we can create rules to avoid the capture of the animals from the nature and use the zoos as vet centers do treat the animals, in this way we will create a learning envoironment for humans and a recovery center for injuried animals. What you think about?
