S Dear Sir, I am writing to complain you about the ban you made public last month. I the last free months there is an issue that dominated among local people. To be more precise, the imposing of a ban on using of mobile phones on public transport system have made many people angry. Moreover, you also made publicaly a ban on using of mobile phones in shops and even expand the ban to restaurants. Firstly, the majority of locals were fed up with your regulations during last two years. Instead of including of your voters to a debate to fing a solution how to tackl the problem, you always make a decision without thinking before. Personally, if I were in the position to give you an assesment, I would give you the lowest rank. Secondly, if we are calling for a better life in our town, we have to have the courage to tackle the problems and not to turn blind eyes on them. What I am trying to say is that locals had came with an idea and arranged a meeting to discuss it and find out a satisfactory outcome appropriate for both sides. Importantly, your presence in the meeting is more then important. So, on behalf of the locals, I am pleased to invite you to discuss our recommendations at the meeting, which is being held at the local pub on May 13th at 6 P.M. We are looking forward to see you there and I do hope, we finally find a solution to our common problem and contribute to a better life in our town. Yours sincerely,
