S Telling the true is one of the way of communication among people. There are many aspects that have impact on our final outcome. Our expressing of the true or a lie depends on if we are talking to an old person, the listeners mood, or even if we are a subordinate to the listener we speak to at the moment. What is acceptable more to tell the true or a lie? Firstly, before making a decision to tell the true or a lie depends how well we know the person who is listen to us. A good illustration of telling the true is supported by our knowledge of the personality of the person we want to speak to. To be more precise, positive attitude and be in a balance with the person we decided to tell the true. Conversely, we intentionally trying to avoid to tell the lies. Instead we are saying things differently or present them in a way which is not clear. As a result, it gives us a chance to put some arguments. The situation can turn against us if we tell the lie at the first try. Finally, to tell the true or a lie depends on the situation and the receiver of our speech. We lie intentionally in order to avoid difficulties, when we knew that our arguments would not be supported by any idea. In my view, it seems reasonable to consider the way we present that something is wrong. When I am in the position to choose the true or a lie, I always trying to see things from diffrent angles, not to turn the blind eye on one side of it. Last but not least, the most important fact in interpersonal communication is to listen and show an interest. This is the most persuasive way to have a positive communication and reach a result, which is beneficial for both sides.
