S Supporting of young people to live an active life is much harder then it was 10 years ago or in my childhood. Many people suffer from not having an active lifestyle severe health problems like obesity. As a good example is that children spend more time on social networks and by playing games on their mobile phones. Do our children need a medication for their addiction to a technology? I am in two minds about it. One one hand, in most cases the technology is not on the blame. In the early childhood, children are equiped by a new technology. What is more, the natural environment in which young children grow and learn is intentionally replaced by the new technology. This arteficial environment support different stimulus of their brains. For instance, they do not think that doing a sport activities is what they need. The simple reason for that is to get from their comfort zone. Getting out of their comfort zone represents efforts and there is no persuasive argument to do it. Some individuals can see a sport activity as a way of relaxing of the body or the brain. Others just want to broke their previous record. Sport activities provide a satisfaction. Conversely, someone can feel it frustrating. On the orher hand, the technology can have a positive effect on our brains. As a evidence of that is using the technology as a tool of education. In my view, sport activities is an important part of our life. It makes us positive if we do some sport activity regularly. BY and large, it keeps us in a good shape. For example, when weget older, we do not relly on others to give us a helping hand. As far as I am concerned, if Iwere in the position to change the lifestyle of the childrem from their childhood, I would have made mandatory to to a sport activity at least 3 times a week. No matter, how old the chidren are. It is our moral responsibility, to do something positive for the health of our childrem. Last but not least, it is no so late to act tommorow.
