S Whether music is essential in our lives might appear like a completely vain question to be asking at first. However I'd like to dig deeper into this topic since I find music crucial for my life moreover I can't remember a day in which music hadn't been a part of. Ancient people used to make sounds which turned into melodies and created first music without even realizing it. There must have been a reason for coming up with a completely new thing such as music. Since then music has taken part in rituals, as celebration but even in comforting someone feeling blue. Needless to say never have I met a person who would have told me they didn't listen to any music. There is no need for a specific genre, every single person listens to something. They might even have the access to the internet yet they involve music by simply singing some melodies in their daily lives. In conclusion yes I do believe music is neccessary for our lives from making us feel understood in those lyrics of songs to motivating us during doing chores.
