S In my opinion the opportunity to live on your own is amazing. I lived with my parents until eighteen years old and after that I ingressed in the university in another city and therefore I needed to live on my own. I learned a lot with this situation, because you need to respect the space of other people and they need to respect your space, other things like to take care of your money, make your food , clean the house and study by yourself is good to prepare you to the future when you will not have your parents to take care of you. I believe that people that don't live this things will suffer more in the future with the routines problems, like job, wife or husband than people that live on your own in the university. When you don't have your parents near of you it's a great time to grow up and take the control of your life. Of course that we have expections, I know some colleagues that studied with me in the past and they didn't live with their parents and therefore they didn't grow up like me but the most colleagues that studied together me grow up fastly and after they finished the course in the university they prefered to keep living on their own. In my opinion when you left your home and live on your own it's very difficult to come back and accepted the rules that your parents want in their home, you want your space and your freedom.
