S To start a discussion about the problem of medical doctors who don't go to rural areas, first we need to talk about a common behavior shared by all humans. Is a main knowledge that our parents teach us since our childhood to be the best person as possible in our lives, it's not unusual for everyone learn things such as the importance of the money to have a good or a comfortable life, we learn to valorize our time to achieve the better position as possible. So, when talk about the medical doctos who choose a comfortable life in the city, where they can earn more money, it easy to undertand why they choose this option. if I were in the same position I will choose the same option. When we think about our life-time, we remember that our life is limited, we have a certain quantity of time to spent, and we need spend this time in the more intelligent way as possible. There are more people living in cities than in rural areas, people who live in cities are more richer than people who live in rural ares, for this reason is not rational choose live in other place. In my opinion, the reasons which make doctors choose live in cities than in rural areas is only rational. It's not normal choose a worse option if you have a better one. But, it is not a rule, there are some medical doctors who choose live in rural ares, these professionals don't need a lot of money. they just want help poor people or want have a peace live living in a place by lifestyle. To sum up, I think this is a personal choose, us as humans and individuals need choose ehat is better for us, despite other opinions.
