S When we talk about offices, we nearly always think about a big room located in a new office building in the center of a city, but this way of thinking is just a steriotype, in many cases the offices are located in places that cannot have the correct infraestructure the company needs to operateo or they just want this place for strategic option. We can't determine a unique layout for all offices because the companies have different realities, some companies need an open plan office to their staff, other companies wants different and separeted spaces to have more control about the interactions for security reasons or business reasons. In my opinion, the reality of work are changing dramatically after Covid-19, many people around the world found a new way to work, they have been starting work from home and liked it, I think the offices will never be the same as they are before 2020, today people feel more confortable working from home, and this workforce behavior is a challenge for traditional business models that impose to their staff to return to the offices, Many people won't return to their old model. We have two main differences in the office work model, the first is a model that involves knowledge, for this type of professionals, share information and experience is more important than work hard alone, the other type of work force, is that people who works in burocractic tasks that not change or witch don't demand creativity, this type of people can work alone for many hours and have no problems with that. Despite the models we have, one thing is very important today, companies need find a way to work that improve the life quality of their employees, if they don't set this as a common goal for the company, they will go out of market.
