S Some high schools have a requirement that students must complete a certain amount of volunteer work in order to graduate. In my opinion this is a good way to improve students' skills, with this practical experince in volunterring they will learn about the importance of charity and will be more socialized professional compared to students which don't have the same experience. When students participate in charity, they learn how important it is for the whole society, a person who has enough time, energy and money to volunter in any activity, will be more respected and recognized than other that have the same opportunity and don't use it to improve. When high schools require that students volunteer for some local work, they are are not only trying improve the quality of poor's life, they are trying dissaminate good actions and improve empathy on students. A person who grow knowing how other persons need their healp, will work better in teams than students who are more antisocial, the action of volunteering is good for everyone, students have a lot of free time and could use this time to do something important. When an employer saw in a resume volunteering work, he imediatelly recognize the importance of that person who are trying to get a job with him, I have no doubts that that task is important for the life of the next generations, they will grow with fundamental values that will change our society to a better way than we improve at this point. This type of requirement must be mandatory in all high schools in each country in the world, this processo certainly would make our world a better place to live.
