S One common topic when we talk about schools requirements is the music class, this is a polemic thing and divide opinions through parents and students. Despite the nobli goal involved in this requirement, some people are not able to play any musical instrument or don't feel comfortable to attend a class where their are obliged to learn how to play a musical instrument. There are schools where students must attend music classes, in other they may not be required, and in some schools may be no music classes at all, In my opinion, schools should offer the possibility to attend a music class, but it should be optional and not a requirement. I will use my example to explain my own point of view, today I'm thirdy years old and don't play any musical instrument. This is not a ploblem to me because I used my time to learn things that is usefull to me, for me know how to play a musical instrument is not an important thing and I'm happy with this decision. If I had been forced to attend a music class when I was at school I certainly would have hated it. Although this arguments, I think music class is an important thing to students who want to learn how to play some instrument. I just think this classes may not be a requirement, it need be optional. Music as art is important for our society, there are many people around the world that love play music and this is not a ploblem, music is a fuel for our mind, the majority of people listen to music every day and this show how important it is for the humanity. To sum up, just learn what make you happy.
