S When we are undergraduates, we are just at the beginning of our life, we don't know many things and we are experiencing new realities, feelings and living new moments that build our personality over time. Some students move away and live on their own wile others choose for live at home with their family, let's talk about this two options. Both options have vantagens and disavantages, the first option improve more experiences to students than the second one, when students decide to live in a campus or rent an apartment close to the university, they will learn how the adult live is, they will understand a reality that was different that they have in their parents house, they will learn things that only the life impose to them. Live alone is a challenge for everyone, but is a great moment when they can grow faster. The second option is more comfortable, when a student keep living at parent's house during college time, they will save more money compared to move away to live in their own. In contrast, many opportunities and experiences will be lost comparatively. Another advantage of living with parents is the fact that they have more free time to focus in the subjects they need learn. Both options are good, sometimes a student doesn't have the option to choose, a student must live with parents because haven't enough money to live by herself for example, sometimes, the parent's hous is much far from the university that student must move away to live more closer and spent less time and money. Despite the options, the most important thing for students is not this short time they will live with parents or not, what matters is learn new things and be happy with what they have at moment.
