S Nowadays, we spend most of our live is spent working at the office. Therefore, it might be utterly useful to analyze which model of office it is better to achive the huge goals that enterprises face in this tough times. In the following lines I will discuss about this issue. On the one hand, it is pretty common to watch people working in enclosed cublicles . Rarely do we find a work place where employees can work in large and pleasant offices like Google's ones. Despite the evidence that this open design offices empower the productivity of enterprises, it seems to me so hard to find somenone like this in our cities. On the other hand, it is widely known that workers can perform better if their employer give them such a comfortable space to work where they are able to see what is going on in the office. As far as I am concerned, feeling being part of the company, workers will give their best to carry on with the daily affair of enterprise. In brief, unless we absolutly change the way we work and where we work it will be hardly difficult to improve the workers life. Hence, it is imperative to reconsider the design of our offices. In this case, I totally believe that open design offices are a good deal better than classical ones. To sum up, I vividly believe that it is time to keep our offices up to date and redesign our work places in order to make them more practical and useful to twenty first thentury needs.
