S Dear Mayor, I am writting in reference to the supposed proprosal of the banning of the use of mobile phones in certain public spaces of our beloved town. As far as I am concerned, this sort of decisions should be discussed with citizens after taking such an important and shocking decision which I totally believe it will have a dramatic impact in our daily live. Firstly, I can arrive to imagine which sorts of security problems our town council want to solve. Seldom do we find someone who is not watching the screen while he is walking or at the bus. Definately, avoiding the use of mobile phones in certain public areas, our town will be a more secure one. However, I am not quite sure if it will be the best chance to fix this issue. Secondly, I reckon that our society needs to disconnect but I consider that this sort of measures are outside the law. In fact, I wonder if it is constitucional. Despite this sort of gadgets can have a negative impact in our society, they had proved to be utterly useful. Therefore, banning them can be not only a catastrophic decision but an inconstitucional one. In brief, we need to change ourselves in order to mend this huge issue. All in all, it is an individual problem with social repercusions. As a result, I consider that another type of measures are needed if we want to improve our city and to boost our quality life. Thank you for considering my application. Kind regards.
