S Telling the truth has been always considerated to many people that are very good persons and they in all ocassions tell the truth of everything, but.... Is always telling the truth the best option? Telling the truth is one of the best options, but not in everything, if you gotta tell that for example, a dog of a person has died and he/she is asking you and you know what happended, you can tell him/her that his/her dog has disappeared to don't make them very sad about their dog has died, but not always telling a lie to try to " fix " something could fix that, it could end up in a very very bad situation, as an example, you can tell that you didn't broke up that jar, but if your mother believes it, she will go to your brother/sister, then to your father and then they will ask you to tell what you saw, and if you lied the punishment of breaking a jar will be bigger as you lied to them too. What you can do to prevent those scenarios you could take like 10 seconds to analize the question the did to you to think about " shall I tell the truth? or a little lie? " then you can say the best option, but in the case you couldn't think about it you could say " I don't know "
