S Hey, Alex I hope you are fine. I am writing you because I should tell you something. I know your party this Saturday afternoon, but I won't come. I'm sorry to say that. Let me tell you why. You know as well as I do that my grandmother is very sick. She was taken into the intensive care unit in the past few days. The doctors said it was getting worse, and I had to be prepared for anything. This morning, the news of her death reached me. I knew I would be lost her but, you know, she is my favorite person, and she was my only family. We may meet next month because I need to be alone for a while. Please don't worry about me. I will be better than now. This party is crucial for you, so you focus on it. Have a good time at your party.
