S Hello, I heard about a plan to ban the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants, who have this idea? I ask it because there are no possibility to people not use their mobile phones in this places. What the person who propose this was thinking? Today we use our smartphone to do a lot of things, some people pay the public transport ticket with an app, use virtual reality to try on clothes and use their cameras to acess restaurant menus through QR codes displayed on the tables. there are no laws that will restrict the use of people smartphones in any place, there are only one place where people don't use their smartphones, I'm talking about high secure areas where these devices are restricted by law. If the intentions of this plan is reduce the use of mobile phones to improve people life quality, baning it is not the right answer. We need teach people about the healp problems the use of their smarphones for loung cours cause on their health, we can stablish social hebavior rules to some places, not to force people do what we whant, but to achive our goals making people choosen themselves the right behavior in that places. We just have to make suggestions to create the right culture, people abits will change naturally to fit to the local culture. This is the right way to influence them do what we want.
