S Hi Alex, I hope you're well. Thank you for your invitation to the party this Saturday. I am afraid that I can't come because I have already had an appointment with my parents who are living separately. They have an 25th wedding anniversary next month. Before that my sister and I decided to give a small gift to them. We will have one night stay at the Ritz London. We started planning this event a few months ago. We didn't even mention this surprise to them. Everything is going under secret. We are so exccited to see our parents surprised. Honestly I am very sorry for the party in the other hand either. I haven't seen you for a long time and the party would give me a great opportunity to reunion with my collage frieds. I want to know how they have been. I will have some free time next month. So I would like seeing you. Why don't you eat out together. Please let me know when is available for you. One more thing, I ask you to say hello to everyone instead of me at the party. Hope you have a wonderful time. Melon
