S Dear Anna, I'm glad to have news from you. I'm learning English for two reasons, first of all in my last travel to London I had to use a lot this language and I couldn't because I had not started with it yet, and I told me "If I had learnt English, I could speak with people." The second reason is that I want to learn it and I want to have more opportunities in my job, because nowadays English is very important and in the future I will ask for a job abroad and if I don't have the level required, I will not able to require the job. Finally, everybody knows that there are better opportunities abroad that in our country. Drop me a line.
