S Dear Jack, First of all I want to say "Happy Birthday" for your birthday again, like I said last week, I really hope you had a great time with your friends and relatives, and you came back home from the restaurant without any accidents. Secondly, we have a very similar way to celebrate our birthdays in my country, but we usually celebrate our parties in our own homes. There, we usually put ballons on the walls a small board with little messages from friends and relatives. At home we have celebrated several parties this year and the way was the same in all of them, but next year we will celebrate them in a restaurant like you, because I think that it's better in that way. Finally if you had any doubt about what I said you, I would explain you in easier way. Drop me a line,
