S Hello there, As in this magazine is looking for some reviews, I'm lending to you reader, my review about Write And Improve. The way I found it, I was looking for some ways to improve my English, why? because the English is the most speaken language and I wanted to do something with it. Now, the interesting part about the review. The first step is a common step, just sign in or log in, after it, you could see at the up left corner, " Welcome (your name) and a sign out button in blue, as it says, it's to sign out from your account, down it you " ll see " W&I woorkbooks " just click there to open every type of workbook that W&I has. down it, when you close W&I workbooks, you'll see a test zone. There is the IELTS Academic test, IELTS General Training adn B2 First. These are official test of Englisht (not certificated ones). Down it you'll see " My workbooks'. " My workbooks " Is for creating a new workbook or joining a workbook, down it you'll see " Create a workbook " and as it name says. It's for creating a workbook, down it you'll see " Join a workbook, and that is just to join a workbook, even tehre is more than you thought, there's still more things to see. Down join a workbook is " Class View " . For now that's for teachers, that helps teachers to see what their students have done, after you'll see Progress, My account and Help centre. Progress is to see your achievements of W&I, my account is for looking your profile with more detail, and help centre is for asking for some help, or reporting any errors. Why did I wrote all that text if you could practice that? Easy, because this is a review of my experience and I wanted to say to English learners that just found W&I. Anyways. Taking my experience with W&I, I could just say that, there aren't many errors as in other websites. The important things are very easy placed and very comfortable to you to foundin them. So that's it. Thank you for reading learner/teacher of English. Good day.
